answers.answer: There is a very good site, LabTestsonline, that has a great amount of information and I found this listing of possibilities if the protein electrophoresis numbers  are low or high.http://labtestsonline.org/understanding/analytes/electrophoresis/tab/testThey are also very helpful in answering questions if you have any - just use the link on their page - and they may be able to help.I'm sorry I can't give any suggestions as to what you might be looking at - I trust your doctor won't just say 'I don't know' and get you some real answers.Feel free to come back if you have more questions,L

question: Hi, I am 29 yrs. old and I have diabetes type 1 and was diagnosed about 8 yrs. ago. About 4 years ago my vision started to gradually decline and about a year and a half ago I began to get strong headaches and eyeaches constantly almost everyday. About eight months ago I had an MRI and it came back negative. A month ago I had a spinal tap and the results came out like this: CSF Index: CSF IGG   *40.40 mg/dL,  CSF Albumin    *110.00 mg/dL,    CSF Ratio  *0.37      Serum IGG   1380.00     Serum Albumin   4760.00   Index  *1.28.  My doctor doesn't know what can be causing this and he has ruled out MS. He has ordered blood work but everything has come back negative. What do you think all this may mean?
title: Elevated test results from spinal tap
